    "summary": "ethos.com exposes one documented REST API surface for its insurance product page, while the developer integration surface actually published by the Ethos brand found here is the Ethos Network HTTP API at `https://api.ethos.network/api/v2`, authenticated with either an Ethos API key or a short-lived Privy bearer token, plus a required `X-Ethos-Client` header.",
    "description": "Ethos.com is a life insurance and estate-planning company website with a partner API marketing page. The developer docs discovered under the Ethos brand describe Ethos Network, a web3 credibility/reputation network with REST APIs for profiles, reviews, votes, wallets, and related data.",
    "credentials": {
      "ethos_api_key": {
        "type": "api_key",
        "label": "Ethos API key",
        "generateUrl": "https://developers.ethos.network/api-documentation/api-key-authentication",
        "setup": "Create an Ethos profile at [app.ethos.network](https://app.ethos.network) linked to your wallet, then follow the [API Keys guide](https://developers.ethos.network/api-documentation/api-key-authentication). You mint a long-lived key by signing a one-time SIWE message and calling `POST https://api.ethos.network/api/v2/api-keys`; the returned token is then sent as `X-Ethos-Api-Key`. API key access must be enabled for your account.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "ethos_privy_token": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "Ethos Privy session token",
        "generateUrl": "https://app.ethos.network",
        "setup": "Sign in to [app.ethos.network](https://app.ethos.network). For authenticated API calls in an active user session, use the short-lived Privy token described in the [Introduction](https://developers.ethos.network/) and [Log in with Ethos](https://developers.ethos.network/api-documentation/log-in-with-ethos) docs. The docs state it is stored in the `privy-token` cookie for the `app.ethos.network` domain and is sent as `Authorization: Bearer <token>`.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      }
    },
